methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.AVISIT
methods.description: Derived based on windowing algorithm described in SAP, Section 8.2

methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.ADY
methods.description: ADY = ADT - TRTSDT + 1, if ADT>=TRTSDT. ADY = ADT - TRTSDT, if ADT<TRTSDT.

methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.ADT
methods.description: SAS date from QS.QSDTC

methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.BASE
methods.description: QS.QSSTRESN where QS.QSBLFL=Y (QS.VISITNUM=3)

methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.CHG
methods.description: AVAL - BASE

methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.PCHG
methods.description: 100* (CHG/BASE)

methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.ANL01FL
methods.description: If multiple visits fall into the same visit window, then the one closest to the target day is chosen for analysis. These are flagged with ANL01FL="Y".

methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.AWTDIFF
methods.description: Absolute difference between AWTARGET and ADY

methods.name: MT.ADSL.SITEGR1
methods.description: refer to SAP, Section 7.1 - if not pooled then SITEGR1=SITEID. If pooled, SITEGR1 will be 900

methods.name: MT.ADSL.TRTSDT
methods.description: SV.SVSTDTC where SV.VISITNUM=3, converted to SAS date

methods.name: MT.ADSL.TRTEDT
methods.description: The date of final dose (from the CRF) is EX.EXENDTC on the subject's last EX record. If the date of final dose is missing for the subject and the subject discontinued after visit 3, use the date of discontinuation as the date of last dose. Convert the date to a SAS date.

methods.name: MT.ADSL.TRTDURD
methods.description: TRTEDT-TRTSDT+1

methods.name: MT.ADSL.AVGDD
methods.description: CUMDOSE/TRTDURD

methods.name: MT.ADSL.CUMDOSE
methods.description:
For TRT01PN=0 or 54: CUMDOSE=TRT01PN*TRTDURD. 
For TRT01PN=81: CUMDOSE will be based on 
  54 mg per day for the # of days subject was in 1st dosing interval 
    (i.e., Date of visit 4 - TRTSTDT+1 if 1st interval completed, TRTEDT-TRTSTDT+1 if subject discontinued <= Visit 4 (Week 4) and > Visit 3 (Baseline)), 
  81 mg per day for the # of days subject was in 2nd dosing interval 
    (i.e., Date of Visit 12 - Date of Visit 4 if 2nd interval completed, TRTEDT- Date of Visit 4 if subject discontinued <= Visit 12 (Week 24) and > Visit 4), 
  and 54 mg per day for the # of days subject was in 3rd dosing interval 
    (i.e., TRTEDT - Date of Visit 12 if subject continued after Visit 12).

methods.name: MT.ADSL.AGEGR1
methods.description: Grouping of AGE into <65, 65-80, and >80

methods.name: MT.ADSL.SAFFL
methods.description: Y if ITTFL='Y' and TRTSDT ne missing. N otherwise

methods.name: MT.ADSL.ITTFL
methods.description: Y if ARMCD ne ' '. N otherwise

methods.name: MT.ADSL.EFFFL
methods.description: Y if SAFFL='Y AND subject has at least one record in QS for ADAS-Cog with QS.VISITNUM>3 AND at least one record in QS for CIBIC+ with QS.VISITNUM>3, N otherwise

methods.name: MT.ADSL.COMP8FL
methods.description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=8 and TRTEDT>= date of visit 8, N otherwise

methods.name: MT.ADSL.COMP16FL
methods.description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=10 and TRTEDT>=date of visit 10, N otherwise

methods.name: MT.ADSL.COMP24FL
methods.description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=12 and TRTEDT>= date of visit 12 , N otherwise

methods.name: MT.ADSL.DISCONFL
methods.description: Y if EOSSTT='DISCONTINUED'. Null otherwise

methods.name: MT.ADSL.DSRAEFL
methods.description: Y if DCSREAS='Adverse Event'. Null otherwise

methods.name: MT.ADSL.BMIBL
methods.description: WEIGHTBL / ((HEIGHTBL*100)**2)

methods.name: MT.ADSL.BMIBLGR1
methods.description: BMIBLGR1=Normal if . < BMIBL <25. BMIBLGR1=Overweight if 25 <=BMIBL <30. BMIBLGR1=Obese if BMIBL >=30

methods.name: MT.ADSL.HEIGHTBL
methods.description: VS.VSSTRESN where VS.VSTESTCD='HEIGHT' and VS.VISITNUM=1

methods.name: MT.ADSL.WEIGHTBL
methods.description: VS.VSSTRESN where VS.VSTESTCD='WEIGHT' and VS.VISITNUM=3

methods.name: MT.ADSL.EDUCLVL
methods.description: SC.SCSTRESN where SC.SCTESTCD="EDLEVEL"

methods.name: MT.ADSL.DISONDT
methods.description: MH.MHSTDTC where MH.MHCAT='PRIMARY DIAGNOSIS' converted to SAS date

methods.name: MT.ADSL.DURDIS
methods.description: number of months between Date of VISIT 1 and DISONDT

methods.name: MT.ADSL.DURDSGR1
methods.description: grouping DURDIS values as <12 and >=12

methods.name: MT.ADSL.VISIT1DT
methods.description: SV.SVSTDTC where SV.VISITNUM=1, converted to SAS date

methods.name: MT.ADSL.VISNUMEN
methods.description: If DS.VISITNUM=13 where DS.DSTERM='PROTOCOL COMPLETED' then VISNUMEN=12, otherwise VISNUMEN=DS.VISITNUM where DS.DSTERM='PROTOCOL COMPLETED'

methods.name: MT.ADSL.RFENDT
methods.description: RFENDTC converted to SAS date

methods.name: MT.ADSL.EOSSTT
methods.description: If DS.DSDECOD='COMPLETED' then EOSSTT='COMPLETED'. Otherwise EOSSTT='DISCONTINUED'.

methods.name: MT.ADSL.DCSREAS
methods.description: If DS.DSCAT='DISPOSITION EVENT' and DS.DSTERM in('I/E NOT MET' 'SPONSOR DECISION' 'WITHDREW CONSENT') then DCSREAS=DS.DSTERM. Otherwise if DS.DSCAT='DISPOSITION EVENT' then DCSREAS=DS.DSDECOD. Convert to mixed case to match display format.

methods.name: MT.ADSL.MMS1TSBL
methods.description: Sum of FT.FTSTRESN values where FT.FTCAT="MMSE" for the subject (FT.FTTESTCD= 'MMS101A'-'MMS111')

methods.name: MT.ADQSADAS.AVAL.ACTOT
methods.description: Sum of ADAS scores for items 1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 11, 12, 13, and 14, see ADRG for details on adjusting for missing values.

methods.name: MT.ADAE.ASTDT
methods.description: AE.AESTDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date. Some events with partial dates are imputed in a conservative manner. If the day component is missing, a value of '01' is used. If both the month and day are missing no imputation is performed as these dates clearly indicate a start prior to the beginning of treatment. There are no events with completely missing start dates.

methods.name: MT.ADAE.ASTDTF
methods.description: ASTDTF='D' if the day value within the character date is imputed. Note that only day values needed to be imputed for this study

methods.name: MT.ADAE.ASTDY
methods.description: IF ASTDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>ASTDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AENDT
methods.description: AE.AEENDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AENDY
methods.description: IF AENDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>AENDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT

methods.name: MT.ADAE.ADURN
methods.description: ADURN=AENDT-ASTDT+1

methods.name: MT.ADAE.ADURU
methods.description: If ADURN is not missing then ADURU='DAY'

methods.name: MT.ADAE.TRTEMFL
methods.description: If ASTDT >= TRTSDT > . then TRTEMFL='Y'. Otherwise TRTEMFL='N'

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AOCCFL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCFL=Y) within each Subject

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AOCCSFL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCSFL=Y) within each Subject and SOC

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AOCCPFL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCPFL=Y) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AOCC02FL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC02FL=Y) within each Subject

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AOCC03FL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC03FL=Y) within each Subject and SOC

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AOCC04FL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC04FL=Y) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

methods.name: MT.ADAE.CQ01NAM
methods.description: If AEDECOD contains any of the character strings of ('APPLICATION', 'DERMATITIS', 'ERYTHEMA', 'BLISTER') OR if AEBODSYS='SKIN AND SUBC UTANEOUS TISSUE DISORDERS' but AEDECOD is not in ('COLD SWEAT', 'HYPERHIDROSIS', 'ALOPECIA') then CQ01NAM='DERMATOLOGIC EVENTS' Otherwise CQ01NAM=NULL

methods.name: MT.ADAE.AOCC01FL
methods.description: Subset to CQ01NAM='' and TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC01FL=Y) within each Subject (Flag First Treatment Emergent Dermatological Event for Time to Event Analysis)

analyses.description: Linear model analysis of CHG for dose response; using randomized dose (0 for placebo; 54 for low dose; 81 for high dose) and site group in model. Used PROC GLM in SAS to produce p-value (from Type III SS for treatment dose).

ANCOVA analysis of CHG performed to provide pairwise comparisons among treatment groups and adjusted means; using randomized treatment as class variable and site group as class variable in model and the baseline value as a covariate.

Unique count of subjects that experienced an Adverse Event by Preferred Term, System Organ Class, and Treatment Group and percentages based on the number of subjects in the safety population within each treatment group. The total number of times an event occurred was recorded by Preferred Term, System Organ Class, and Treatment Group. Fisher's exact test was used for treatment comparison of event rates.
